[
  {
    "text": "I had a friend,",
    "start": 5.585,
    "duration": 1.251
  },
  {
    "text": "a songwriting mentor\nand a great songwriter, John Stewart,",
    "start": 6.878,
    "duration": 4.63
  },
  {
    "text": "who told me just before he died,",
    "start": 11.55,
    "duration": 4.129
  },
  {
    "text": "\"We are all just radios,",
    "start": 15.72,
    "duration": 3.045
  },
  {
    "text": "hoping to pick up each other's signals.\"",
    "start": 18.765,
    "duration": 3.17
  },
  {
    "text": "I found that to be true and profound.",
    "start": 23.103,
    "duration": 3.753
  },
  {
    "text": "And I've spent my life\ntrying to clear the static.",
    "start": 27.274,
    "duration": 3.128
  },
  {
    "text": "The strongest signals\nthat come to me are musical",
    "start": 32.237,
    "duration": 3.503
  },
  {
    "text": "in the form of songs or stories\ntold in rhythm and rhyme.",
    "start": 35.782,
    "duration": 5.047
  },
  {
    "text": "Sometimes I can tune in\nto a revolution in the heart.",
    "start": 42.33,
    "duration": 5.589
  },
  {
    "text": "Sometimes I hear a keen\nfrom my Celtic ancestors.",
    "start": 50.38,
    "duration": 4.755
  },
  {
    "text": "And some songs have been\npostcards from my future.",
    "start": 55.969,
    "duration": 4.713
  },
  {
    "text": "In my family, there was a song\nfor every loss, every celebration,",
    "start": 64.436,
    "duration": 4.379
  },
  {
    "text": "every unspoken need, every longing.",
    "start": 68.857,
    "duration": 2.878
  },
  {
    "text": "But there was also so much chaos\nthat often I was the only one",
    "start": 73.028,
    "duration": 4.462
  },
  {
    "text": "who recognized\nwhat was being communicated.",
    "start": 77.532,
    "duration": 3.087
  },
  {
    "text": "My grandmother, Carrie Cash,",
    "start": 83.538,
    "duration": 4.338
  },
  {
    "text": "moved with my grandfather\nand their five children",
    "start": 87.917,
    "duration": 3.629
  },
  {
    "text": "into a New Deal era colony",
    "start": 91.588,
    "duration": 3.295
  },
  {
    "text": "created by FDR for poor families",
    "start": 94.883,
    "duration": 3.712
  },
  {
    "text": "in the sunken lands\nof the Arkansas Delta in 1935.",
    "start": 98.595,
    "duration": 5.505
  },
  {
    "text": "So they moved into this freshly\npainted cottage,",
    "start": 105.727,
    "duration": 4.046
  },
  {
    "text": "and she gave birth\nto two more babies there",
    "start": 109.814,
    "duration": 3.796
  },
  {
    "text": "with the assistance only of a doctor",
    "start": 113.652,
    "duration": 2.127
  },
  {
    "text": "who came by in a horse and buggy",
    "start": 115.779,
    "duration": 2.544
  },
  {
    "text": "and pulled two loose aspirin\nfrom his pocket to give to her.",
    "start": 118.365,
    "duration": 4.671
  },
  {
    "text": "The same pocket in which he kept\nhis fishing worms.",
    "start": 123.995,
    "duration": 3.796
  },
  {
    "text": "(Laughter)",
    "start": 127.791,
    "duration": 1.585
  },
  {
    "text": "That's true.",
    "start": 131.795,
    "duration": 1.293
  },
  {
    "text": "(Laughter)",
    "start": 133.088,
    "duration": 1.293
  },
  {
    "text": "I read once that every time\nan old woman dies,",
    "start": 135.59,
    "duration": 4.963
  },
  {
    "text": "a library disappears.",
    "start": 140.553,
    "duration": 2.336
  },
  {
    "text": "And before her library disappeared,",
    "start": 145.141,
    "duration": 2.127
  },
  {
    "text": "I tuned into my grandmother's signals",
    "start": 147.31,
    "duration": 3.128
  },
  {
    "text": "and gleaned her tenacity",
    "start": 150.48,
    "duration": 6.256
  },
  {
    "text": "which I borrowed,",
    "start": 156.778,
    "duration": 1.627
  },
  {
    "text": "and her long suffering in her life\nof constant work with seven children,",
    "start": 160.156,
    "duration": 5.506
  },
  {
    "text": "six of whom made it to adulthood.",
    "start": 165.704,
    "duration": 2.502
  },
  {
    "text": "In a house without electricity.",
    "start": 169.374,
    "duration": 3.378
  },
  {
    "text": "In the sweltering cotton fields,",
    "start": 174.254,
    "duration": 2.878
  },
  {
    "text": "and I wrote these words about her.",
    "start": 177.173,
    "duration": 2.086
  },
  {
    "text": "(Music)",
    "start": 179.3,
    "duration": 2.378
  },
  {
    "text": "(Singing) Five cans of paint",
    "start": 181.678,
    "duration": 3.211
  },
  {
    "text": "in the empty fields",
    "start": 184.889,
    "duration": 2.586
  },
  {
    "text": "And the dust reveals",
    "start": 188.643,
    "duration": 2.544
  },
  {
    "text": "And the children cry",
    "start": 196.443,
    "duration": 3.545
  },
  {
    "text": "the work never ends",
    "start": 199.988,
    "duration": 2.794
  },
  {
    "text": "There’s not a single friend",
    "start": 203.908,
    "duration": 2.586
  },
  {
    "text": "Who will hold her hand",
    "start": 212.208,
    "duration": 3.796
  },
  {
    "text": "in the sunken lands?",
    "start": 216.004,
    "duration": 3.128
  },
  {
    "text": "And the mud and tears\nmelt the cotton balls",
    "start": 236.524,
    "duration": 6.382
  },
  {
    "text": "It’s a heavy toll",
    "start": 244.491,
    "duration": 1.876
  },
  {
    "text": "Oh, oh",
    "start": 247.494,
    "duration": 1.293
  },
  {
    "text": "His words are cruel",
    "start": 251.956,
    "duration": 3.504
  },
  {
    "text": "and they sting like fire",
    "start": 255.502,
    "duration": 2.585
  },
  {
    "text": "Like the devil’s choir",
    "start": 259.464,
    "duration": 2.419
  },
  {
    "text": "Oh, oh",
    "start": 262.675,
    "duration": 1.627
  },
  {
    "text": "Who will hold her hand",
    "start": 267.639,
    "duration": 3.712
  },
  {
    "text": "in the sunken lands?",
    "start": 271.351,
    "duration": 3.336
  },
  {
    "text": "(Music)",
    "start": 275.355,
    "duration": 4.796
  },
  {
    "text": "The river rises and she sails away",
    "start": 291.955,
    "duration": 5.797
  },
  {
    "text": "She could never stay",
    "start": 299.462,
    "duration": 2.086
  },
  {
    "text": "Oh, oh",
    "start": 302.757,
    "duration": 1.376
  },
  {
    "text": "Now her work is done",
    "start": 307.011,
    "duration": 3.963
  },
  {
    "text": "in the sunken lands",
    "start": 311.015,
    "duration": 3.587
  },
  {
    "text": "There’s five empty cans",
    "start": 315.937,
    "duration": 3.545
  },
  {
    "text": "(Music)",
    "start": 319.858,
    "duration": 4.713
  },
  {
    "text": "(Music ends)",
    "start": 336.082,
    "duration": 2.377
  },
  {
    "text": "(Applause)",
    "start": 340.753,
    "duration": 5.548
  },
  {
    "text": "In 1992,",
    "start": 351.848,
    "duration": 2.419
  },
  {
    "text": "I was writing a song about my divorce,",
    "start": 354.309,
    "duration": 3.461
  },
  {
    "text": "which hadn't happened yet.",
    "start": 357.77,
    "duration": 1.752
  },
  {
    "text": "(Laughter)",
    "start": 359.564,
    "duration": 1.877
  },
  {
    "text": "But which I saw coming\nlike a freight train.",
    "start": 361.441,
    "duration": 4.087
  },
  {
    "text": "(Laughter)",
    "start": 365.528,
    "duration": 2.586
  },
  {
    "text": "So I was stuck in this song",
    "start": 369.616,
    "duration": 2.836
  },
  {
    "text": "like I was stuck in my life.",
    "start": 372.452,
    "duration": 3.128
  },
  {
    "text": "And the same time across the country,",
    "start": 375.622,
    "duration": 3.545
  },
  {
    "text": "my mother was going through a box\nof my school assignments",
    "start": 379.167,
    "duration": 3.879
  },
  {
    "text": "and childhood drawings,",
    "start": 383.087,
    "duration": 3.42
  },
  {
    "text": "and she sent it to me.",
    "start": 386.549,
    "duration": 1.71
  },
  {
    "text": "So I started going through this box,\nand I came across this yellowed paper,",
    "start": 388.301,
    "duration": 4.087
  },
  {
    "text": "this school assignment I had done\nin the seventh grade",
    "start": 392.43,
    "duration": 4.671
  },
  {
    "text": "in Catholic school",
    "start": 397.143,
    "duration": 1.96
  },
  {
    "text": "on metaphors and similes.",
    "start": 399.103,
    "duration": 3.087
  },
  {
    "text": "Now I vividly remember the pleasure\nI took in that assignment",
    "start": 403.316,
    "duration": 5.297
  },
  {
    "text": "because it was literally the only thing",
    "start": 408.613,
    "duration": 2.085
  },
  {
    "text": "the nuns had ever given me\nto do that I enjoyed.",
    "start": 410.74,
    "duration": 2.92
  },
  {
    "text": "(Laughter)",
    "start": 413.701,
    "duration": 2.419
  },
  {
    "text": "So this line I had written\npopped out at me.",
    "start": 418.873,
    "duration": 2.961
  },
  {
    "text": "\"A lonely road is a bodyguard.\"",
    "start": 423.211,
    "duration": 3.336
  },
  {
    "text": "What did it mean?",
    "start": 429.384,
    "duration": 1.376
  },
  {
    "text": "I had even pasted a picture\nof this empty road",
    "start": 432.178,
    "duration": 3.17
  },
  {
    "text": "next to the line.",
    "start": 435.39,
    "duration": 2.002
  },
  {
    "text": "It was a metaphor.",
    "start": 437.892,
    "duration": 1.293
  },
  {
    "text": "It wasn't \"a lonely road\nis like a bodyguard,\" a simile.",
    "start": 440.979,
    "duration": 5.839
  },
  {
    "text": "It was the much more poetic:\n“A lonely road is a bodyguard.”",
    "start": 447.652,
    "duration": 4.963
  },
  {
    "text": "As painful as that was then,\nand as it still can be painful now,",
    "start": 455.368,
    "duration": 6.006
  },
  {
    "text": "I knew what she was telling me.",
    "start": 461.374,
    "duration": 1.96
  },
  {
    "text": "That ...",
    "start": 463.376,
    "duration": 1.126
  },
  {
    "text": "Solitude can protect\nthe seeds of creativity.",
    "start": 465.628,
    "duration": 4.505
  },
  {
    "text": "And that loneliness contains\na priceless gift",
    "start": 470.925,
    "duration": 5.506
  },
  {
    "text": "if we can tolerate the initial discomfort",
    "start": 476.472,
    "duration": 4.505
  },
  {
    "text": "and avoid the seduction of despair.",
    "start": 481.019,
    "duration": 3.503
  },
  {
    "text": "So my 12-year-old waved at me\nacross the decades,",
    "start": 486.024,
    "duration": 4.004
  },
  {
    "text": "saying that who I was",
    "start": 490.069,
    "duration": 3.337
  },
  {
    "text": "was who I would become.",
    "start": 493.448,
    "duration": 2.127
  },
  {
    "text": "And I waved back",
    "start": 496.409,
    "duration": 1.668
  },
  {
    "text": "and I dropped her line\nright in the song I was writing.",
    "start": 498.119,
    "duration": 5.172
  },
  {
    "text": "(Singing) I’ll send the angels\nto watch over you tonight",
    "start": 503.291,
    "duration": 5.964
  },
  {
    "text": "And you send them right back to me",
    "start": 509.756,
    "duration": 3.712
  },
  {
    "text": "A lonely road is a bodyguard",
    "start": 515.094,
    "duration": 3.712
  },
  {
    "text": "If we really want it to be",
    "start": 520.475,
    "duration": 2.043
  },
  {
    "text": "(Music ends)",
    "start": 522.56,
    "duration": 1.251
  },
  {
    "text": "We're all just radios",
    "start": 525.313,
    "duration": 3.628
  },
  {
    "text": "hoping to pick up each other's signals.",
    "start": 528.983,
    "duration": 3.045
  },
  {
    "text": "And some of those signals\nhave a backbeat and a melody,",
    "start": 532.445,
    "duration": 4.129
  },
  {
    "text": "and they're universal.",
    "start": 536.574,
    "duration": 1.71
  },
  {
    "text": "And music can unlock a frozen memory",
    "start": 538.951,
    "duration": 3.879
  },
  {
    "text": "that melts into the seeds\nof our creativity.",
    "start": 542.872,
    "duration": 3.337
  },
  {
    "text": "And the reverse is also true.",
    "start": 547.251,
    "duration": 2.294
  },
  {
    "text": "A memory can unlock a song\nthat's waiting to be written.",
    "start": 549.962,
    "duration": 5.631
  },
  {
    "text": "It can reveal us to ourselves\nacross time and generations,",
    "start": 556.803,
    "duration": 5.964
  },
  {
    "text": "in community, in solitude.",
    "start": 562.809,
    "duration": 3.128
  },
  {
    "text": "Some frequencies are sound,",
    "start": 568.397,
    "duration": 3.17
  },
  {
    "text": "and some frequencies are light.",
    "start": 571.609,
    "duration": 2.711
  },
  {
    "text": "And some take a half a lifetime",
    "start": 575.029,
    "duration": 5.13
  },
  {
    "text": "to reach their destination.",
    "start": 580.201,
    "duration": 2.21
  },
  {
    "text": "(Music)",
    "start": 584.122,
    "duration": 3.92
  },
  {
    "text": "(Singing) Light is particle and wave",
    "start": 590.461,
    "duration": 4.755
  },
  {
    "text": "Our histories written large upon the page",
    "start": 598.136,
    "duration": 5.13
  },
  {
    "text": "The star in middle age",
    "start": 604.433,
    "duration": 3.212
  },
  {
    "text": "The love that fades to black",
    "start": 609.23,
    "duration": 2.753
  },
  {
    "text": "Once revealed, won’t be taken back",
    "start": 612.024,
    "duration": 3.671
  },
  {
    "text": "Light nothing can escape",
    "start": 616.07,
    "duration": 4.129
  },
  {
    "text": "The ignorance we once forgave",
    "start": 623.786,
    "duration": 3.796
  },
  {
    "text": "In the future,\nif we don't decide to change",
    "start": 629.959,
    "duration": 5.005
  },
  {
    "text": "The things we cannot save",
    "start": 635.006,
    "duration": 2.794
  },
  {
    "text": "But it slows to shine upon your face",
    "start": 637.8,
    "duration": 4.296
  },
  {
    "text": "We owe everything",
    "start": 642.722,
    "duration": 3.044
  },
  {
    "text": "Everything",
    "start": 647.31,
    "duration": 1.543
  },
  {
    "text": "Everything",
    "start": 650.813,
    "duration": 1.585
  },
  {
    "text": "To this rainbow of suffering",
    "start": 652.773,
    "duration": 2.92
  },
  {
    "text": "Light is particle and wave",
    "start": 657.236,
    "duration": 4.797
  },
  {
    "text": "Refractions of this place",
    "start": 664.827,
    "duration": 3.587
  },
  {
    "text": "Reflections of our grace",
    "start": 671.25,
    "duration": 3.587
  },
  {
    "text": "It reveals what we hold dear",
    "start": 675.671,
    "duration": 3.379
  },
  {
    "text": "And it’s slow so I can hold you near",
    "start": 679.091,
    "duration": 3.629
  },
  {
    "text": "(Music ends)",
    "start": 686.891,
    "duration": 1.126
  },
  {
    "text": "(Applause)",
    "start": 692.438,
    "duration": 5.798
  },
  {
    "text": "There's one thing I know for certain.",
    "start": 698.653,
    "duration": 2.794
  },
  {
    "text": "That we clear the static\nby being vulnerable",
    "start": 701.822,
    "duration": 4.422
  },
  {
    "text": "and by telling the truth.",
    "start": 706.285,
    "duration": 1.752
  },
  {
    "text": "And here we are doing just that.",
    "start": 708.621,
    "duration": 3.17
  },
  {
    "text": "Thank you.",
    "start": 712.667,
    "duration": 1.209
  },
  {
    "text": "(Applause)",
    "start": 713.876,
    "duration": 7.007
  }
]